OL,3,CGuernsey needs more regulation to
OL,4,Csafeguard elections, review says
OL,6,FThey include considering a permanent
OL,7,Felectoral roll that regularly updates,
OL,8,Frather than asking people to register
OL,9,Feach time they want to vote, which the
OL,10,Freport explains "is an administrative
OL,11,Fburden and risks missing some of the
OL,12,Feligible electorate".
OL,14,FIt calls for those standing in an
OL,15,Felection to sign a Code of Conduct
OL,16,Fwhich "could strengthen the integrity
OL,17,Fof the campaign period, promote
OL,18,Frespectful public discourse, and
OL,19,Freinforce candidate accountability".
